kitchen as storage.

00:20:51.430 --> 00:20:53.090
He said, well, it's not worth
my time to learn how to cook,

00:20:53.090 --> 00:20:55.350
because I make more money
working instead of cooking.

00:20:55.350 --> 00:20:57.460
And now he as a kid
and he's like Instagram

00:20:57.460 --> 00:20:59.410
every single thing
that he makes.

00:20:59.410 --> 00:21:01.280
Seriously, same person.

00:21:01.280 --> 00:21:05.745
And he's 40, so when this
young generation is coming up,

00:21:05.745 --> 00:21:09.190
I do think that having that
wonderful access to great food

00:21:09.190 --> 00:21:11.380
at work will influence the
choices that you guys are

00:21:11.380 --> 00:21:11.880
making.

00:21:11.880 --> 00:21:14.420
But I would encourage you
to start that process now.

00:21:14.420 --> 00:21:15.160
Come on out.

00:21:15.160 --> 00:21:16.170
Come on out of Google.

00:21:16.170 --> 00:21:18.790
Like, yeah, there's classes
here and there's stuff here,

00:21:18.790 --> 00:21:20.540
but come on out into
the city, because you

00:21:20.540 --> 00:21:22.910
can have different experiences
and come meet new people

00:21:22.910 --> 00:21:25.860
and learn new things and
discover things you never

00:21:25.860 --> 00:21:27.490
would have expected.

00:21:27.490 --> 00:21:29.240
SAM MOGANNAM: That's
so totally funny,

